    <weatherForecast/>
    <avalancheActivity>
      <highlights>The sleet will give rise from the late morning to moistening of the snowpack in particular at low and intermediate altitudes. Moist snow slides and avalanches are possible.</highlights>
      <comment>Up to 2300 m rain will fall from late morning in some regions. This situation will give rise to significant moistening of the snowpack at low and intermediate altitudes. &lt;br/> &lt;br/> Below approximately 2300 m and on very steep slopes small to medium-sized wet snow slides and avalanches are possible as a consequence of the rain. &lt;br/> In places where the snowfall level is higher the avalanche danger is greater. &lt;br/> &lt;br/> The conditions are unfavourable for ski touring, snowshoe hiking as well as off-piste descents, both due to the strong moistening of the snowpack at mid and low altitudes and due to locally poor visibility.</comment>
    </avalancheActivity>
    <snowpackStructure>
      <comment>Below approximately 2300 m: The surface of the snowpack will only just freeze and will already be soft in the early morning. &lt;br/> The rain will give rise in the afternoon to increasing moistening of the snowpack below approximately 2300 m. This situation will give rise to a loss of strength within the old snowpack.</comment>
    </snowpackStructure>
    <travelAdvisory/>
    <tendency>
      <highlights>A lot of snow will fall on Monday. Increase in avalanche danger as a consequence of the snowfall.</highlights>
      <tendencyType>increasing</tendencyType>
